The Tropical Dome will be lit Purple to support Virtus Oceania Asia Games.

Included Through Sport.&nbsp;

Sport Inclusion Australia is proud to host the inaugural Virtus Oceania Asia Games (OA Games), the largest elite intellectually impaired sporting event being held in Brisbane between 5 - 11 November 2022.&nbsp;
This will be the first time a Virtus Regional Games will be held for the Oceania Asia region, with up to 1000 elite athletes and officials from New Zealand, Asia and Pacific Nations coming to Brisbane to &nbsp;participate in the OA Games in November 2022.

This Light Up is organised by: Brisbane City Council in partnership with Sports Inclusion Australia

The Story Bridge will be lit Blue Purple Red Orange Green to support Virtus Oceania Asia Games.

